# Git, CI & Deployment

## Git
- Commit messages: English only, max 5 words.
- Never add `--trailer "Made-with: Cursor"` or any AI attribution trailers.
- Never commit without explicit user permission.
- Branch strategy: determined per project.

## CI Pipeline (.github/workflows/)
- `ci.yml`: ruff (Python lint), pytest, eslint, vitest, build checks.
- `test.yml`: test suite execution.
- Security: Snyk, Bandit, pip-audit, Safety, Gitleaks, eslint-plugin-security.

## Docker
- Backend: `python:3.12-slim` base, Playwright chromium installed.
- CMD: `alembic upgrade head && uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT` (chain ends at **`009_full_v2_schema_rebuild`**; `app/main.py` lifespan also runs `alembic upgrade head` before bootstrap — idempotent).
- Local dev: `docker-compose.yml` (postgres, redis, backend, celery-worker, celery-beat, frontend).
- Production: `docker-compose.prod.yml`.

## Deployment
- Backend: Railway (3 services: backend, celery-worker, celery-beat).
- Frontend: Cloudflare Pages.
- Database: Supabase PostgreSQL.
- Cache/Broker: Upstash Redis.
- Deploy trigger: git push → Railway auto-build.

## Environment Variables
- Use only `.env` file — no `.env.local`, `.env.sample`, `.env.example` variations.
- All secrets via environment variables. Never commit secrets.
- Key variables: DATABASE_URL, REDIS_URL, JWT_SECRET, CLAUDE_API_KEY, DECODO_USERNAME, DECODO_PASSWORD, DECODO_ENABLED, TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET, RESEND_API_KEY.
